no.motif.f.combine

Class Disjunction<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • no.motif.f.combine.Disjunction<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Predicate<T>

    public class Disjunction<T>
extends Object
implements Predicate<T>
    A disjunction is a composition of several predicates which evaluates to true when at least one of the predicates yields true. If all the predicates evaluates to false, the disjunction is also false.
